name: The Cosmos Will See You Now (Open Cosmos Constellation Launch 1)
location_str: Unknown Pad @ Rocket Lab Launch Complex 1, NZL
description: First 2 satellites of UK-based Open Cosmos' secure LEO broadband constellation designed to provide independent and resilient connectivity infrastructure for Europe and the world, using high-priority Ka-band spectrum filings by the Principality of Liechtenstein.
rocket_fact: Specific Impulse (ISP) is the 'miles per gallon' of rocketry, measuring how efficiently an engine turns fuel into thrust.
